President Trump and Prime Minister Khan of Pakistan held a joint press conference in New York. They discussed various topics, including trade, the Taliban and Afghanistan, and the situation in Kashmir. President Trump expressed his willingness to mediate between India and Pakistan over the Kashmir issue if both countries agreed. He also praised Pakistan's progress in countering terrorism and expressed his trust in Prime Minister Khan. The leaders also discussed the possibility of resuming talks with the Taliban and the humanitarian crisis in Kashmir. Prime Minister Khan called on President Trump to use his influence to resolve the situation in Kashmir.